{
  "texts": [
    "In graph data, the design of graph pooling is more complex because there is no regular spatial layout in graph data.",
    "The basic principle is to selectively reduce the number of nodes or aggregate node features of the graph while preserving the overall structure and important features of the graph (Zhang et al. 2021b).",
    "The role of graph pooling in graph neural networks is primarily to reduce graph complexity and capture global or higher-level graph structure information.",
    "Specifically, its role includes:",
    "Optimizing Feature Extraction and Improving Computational Efficiency: By aggregating node features and substructures, graph pooling extracts a condensed graph representation rich in global and higher-order information (Duval and Malliaros 2022)."
  ]
}